  "Regulator Statement" : "WITHOUT ADMITTING OR DENYING THE ALLEGATIONS, BIDDICK CONSENTED TO THE DESCRIBED SANCTIONS AND TO THE ENTRY OF FINDINGS, THEREFORE, HE IS FINED $5,000, JOINTLY AND SEVERALLY.   FINES PAID ON MAY 30, 2000.",
  "Broker Comment" : "ACTING AS CFO, ENCHARGED WITH ALL RESPONSIBILITIES RELATIVE TO THE MAINTENANCE OF NET CAPITAL FOR A MARKET MAKING MEMBER FIRM (CENTEX), IT WAS DETERMINED THAT THE FIRM WAS MAKING MARKETS FOR NINE CALENDAR DAYS, SEPTEMBER 1, 1999 THROUGH SEPTEMBER 9, 1999, IN VIOLATION OF A TECHNICAL MINIMUM NET CAPITAL REQUIREMENT. IN APRIL 1999, CENTEX ELECTED TO CHANGE CLEARING FIRMS FROM FIRST SOUTHWEST COMPANY (FSW) TO EMMETT A. LARKIN (EAL).  DURING THE CHANGE FSW WITHHELD THE TRANSFER OF $205,821.99 WHICH WAS HELD AS A CLEARING DEPOSIT.  THE REASON GIVEN BY FSW FOR WITHHOLDING THESE FUNDS WAS TO OFFSET ANY CONTINGENT LIABILITY WHICH FSW FELT MAY OR MAY NOT SURFACE IN THE FUTURE. WITHOUT EITHER WRITTEN OR ORAL NOTIFICATION FSW JOURNALED THE $205,821.99 FROM AN ACCOUNT CONTROLLED BY CENTEX TO AN ACCOUNT CONTROLLED BY FSW ON AUGUST 31, 1999. I WAS MADE AWARE THAT THE $205,821.99 HAD BEEN JOURNALED OUT OF THE CENTEX ACCOUNT ON SEPTEMBER 9, 1999 WHEN THE REQUIRED QUARTERLY ACCOUNT STATEMENT ARRIVED IN THE MAIL.  I IMMEDIATELY AFFECTED THE DROPPING OF MARKET MAKING ACTIVITIES FOR CENTEX AND MADE PROPER WRITTEN NOTIFICATION TO THE SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION (SEC) AND THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF SECURITIES DEALERS (NASD) OF THE MARKET MAKING WITHDRAWAL DUE TO NET CAPITAL DEFICIENCIES.  AS OF THIS WRITING FSW CONTINUES TO HOLD THE $205,821.00 DEPOSIT. LITIGATION WITH RESPECT TO THE ILLEGAL CONVERSION OF FUNDS IS CURRENTLY UNDERWAY BY CENTEX AGAINST FIRST SOUTHWEST COMPANY. "
